What POCO actually is
    POCO is a collection of backend/system-level C++ libraries. It focuses on:
        Networking (HTTP, TCP, WebSocket)
        Multithreading
        File system & OS abstraction
        JSON, XML
        Logging
        Utilities

Think of it as:
    “C++ version of backend/infrastructure toolkit”

Simple mental model
    POCO = backend + system layer
    Qt/wxWidgets = frontend (GUI)
--------------------------------------------
POCO C++ Libraries examples

Install in Ubuntu 18 ->

    sudo apt update
    sudo apt install libpoco-dev

Verify Installation ->

Check if the Poco header files and libraries are installed in 

    /usr/include/Poco/ and
    /usr/lib/

check version
    dpkg -l | grep libpoco

--------------------------------------------
Manjaro(arch) Linux -->

    sudo pacman -S poco

Verify Installation
    Check headers and libraries

        pacman -Ql poco | grep include
        pacman -Ql poco | grep lib
----------------------------------------------



